M_SCT[1479]='449. So I have heard. At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.';
M_SCT[1480]='Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita came out of retreat, went to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him. When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Sāriputta:';
M_SCT[1481]='“Reverend, they speak of ‘a witless person’. How is a witless person defined?”';
M_SCT[1482]='“Reverend, they’re called witless because they don’t understand. And what don’t they understand? They don’t understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’ They’re called witless because they don’t understand.”';
M_SCT[1483]='Saying “Good, reverend,” Mahākoṭṭhita approved and agreed with what Sāriputta said. Then he asked another question:';
M_SCT[1484]='450. “They speak of this thing called ‘feeling’. How is feeling defined?”';
M_SCT[1485]='“It’s called feeling because it feels. And what does it feel? It feels pleasure, pain, and neutral. It’s called feeling because it feels.”';
M_SCT[1486]='“They speak of this thing called ‘perception’. How is perception defined?”';
M_SCT[1487]='“It’s called perception because it perceives. And what does it perceive? It perceives blue, yellow, red, and white. It’s called perception because it perceives.”';
M_SCT[1488]='“Feeling, perception, and consciousness— are these things mixed or separate? And can we completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them?”';
M_SCT[1489]='“Feeling, perception, and consciousness— these things are mixed, not separate. And you can never completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them. For you perceive what you feel, and you cognize what you perceive. That’s why these things are mixed, not separate. And you can never completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them.”';
M_SCT[1490]='“Wisdom and consciousness— what is the difference between these things that are mixed, not separate?”';
M_SCT[1491]='451. “What can be known by purified mind consciousness released from the five senses?”';
M_SCT[1492]='“Aware that ‘space is infinite’ it can know the dimension of infinite space. Aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’ it can know the dimension of infinite consciousness. Aware that ‘there is nothing at all’ it can know the dimension of nothingness.”';
M_SCT[1493]='“How do you understand something that can be known?”';
M_SCT[1494]='452. “How many conditions are there for the arising of right view?”';
M_SCT[1495]='“There are two conditions for the arising of right view: the words of another and proper attention. These are the two conditions for the arising of right view.”';
M_SCT[1496]='“When right view is supported by how many factors does it have freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom as its fruit and benefit?”';
M_SCT[1497]='“When right view is supported by five factors it has freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom as its fruit and benefit. It’s when right view is supported by ethics, learning, discussion, serenity, and discernment. When right view is supported by these five factors it has freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom as its fruit and benefit.”';
